    • Method Detail

      • removeChunk

        void removeChunk(IChunk chunk)
        remove chunk from long term memory. This is an optional operation and given the complexities of DM, it's contract is limited. After calling this, the named chunk will no longer be accessible via IDeclarativeModule.getChunk(String), IDeclarativeModule.findExactMatches(org.jactr.core.production.request.ChunkTypeRequest, java.util.Comparator, IChunkFilter) , or ISymbolicChunkType.getChunks(). Any further references to the chunk (e.g. by other chunks) may or may not be replaced by tombstones.
        Parameters:
        chunk -
